<div>
  <p align='center'><font color='#000071' size='4' face='Arial'><b>KUNARK
  MAGICIAN SUMMARY</b></font>
  <p>
  <font face='Arial' size='2'>Well mages, you may have wondered what the
  world of Norrath holds for you now that the new world has opened. Well I don't
  have much of the new lands explored, but I can tell you all about you new
  spells. Almost all of them are right on the money on this site so I'll just
  hut up the highlights.<br>
  <br>
  <b>PETS</b><br>
  Pet may disappoint you at first glance but I feel that they have done
  something truly remarkable with our magician pets. True Variation. The days
  are now gone when we summon a water pet because we are in sol b and LDC are
  immune to fire spells. Here is what I've found our pets to be:<br>
  <br>
  <i>Earth Pets-</i><br>
  Basically the same as other earth pets. Hard to tell but I believe more hp,
  and more strength. I thing that the difference between Earth and the other
  pets is much larger than it was before. Also the new spell Earth Elemental
  Strike is root with a longer range and Level of pet + 10 damage.<br>
  <br>
  <i>Fire Pets-</i><br>
  What the hell is wrong with fire pets? May be the first thing you think upon
  summoning your first Voceration: Fire. Well nothing really, they no longer
  cast FireElementalAura, it's been replace by the pathetic O'Keil's Radiation.
  They also don't cast the FireElementalAttack spell anymore, they are little
  mini wizards, so far I've seen them cast: Lightning, Shock of Force, some stun
  spell, and both a hot and a cold spell. I believe that fire pets cast either
  34 or 39 spells but that is going to take more investigation. The biggest
  problem with fire pets is they are no longer tanks at all, without the old
  elemental aura for Level of pet + 1 damage, and the long cast wizard spells,
  you really don't want to summon this pet too much solo.<br>
  <br>
  <i>Air Pets-</i><br>
  Not much new about air pets as far as I've been able to tell. Their stun now
  does damage (Level + 10) and seems to last a little longer, and I think the
  base delay of air pets may have been reduced. I'm not much of a number
  cruncher so I can't say for sure.<br>
  <br>
  <i>Water Pets</i><br>
  Water pets haven't changed all that much. Their water strike spell now does
  (level+10)X 2. but the nicest thing about water pets is seeing them backstab.
  I've seen water pets backstab for up to 200 damage, but that may not be the
  cap, who knows.<br>
  <br>
  <i>D yzil's Deafening Decoy-</i><br>
  And what the hell is this you may ask. Well a summoned decoy is a truly unique
  idea for pets. The Decoy looks like a big fire pet, and focus items don't seem
  to work on it. It has a much lower damage potential than other pets, but seems
  to have even more hp than earth pets. The decoy now casts the old
  FireElementalAura spell, but the neatest thing about the Decoy is it's super
  taunt AoE spell. It didn't seem to be 100% functional last time I played with
  it, but this is supposed to get creatures REALLY mad at your pet to let you
  nuke, run or what have you. I suspect this one will be VERY popular with
  enchanters in places like Sol B, Guk, and all the fun new train dungeons that
  Kunark will have for us. Careful, this spell has a very long Recycle Time.<br>
  <br>
  <i>Rage Of Zomm</i><br>
  Summons a Holy Hand Grenade = ). Basically just a guided eye that blows things
  up. Well I assume at least, at first the spell summoned pets named !Kibaer
  that ran all the way across the zone and bugged you so you couldn't summon
  another pet, now pets just die as soon as you summoned them in a little explosion
  that doesn't seem to really hurt anymore.<br>
  <br>
  <b>ITEM SUMMONS</b><br>
  Well some of these are pretty boring, other not so much. I'll leave it to you
  to decide.<br>
  <br>
  <i>Gift of Xev</i><br>
  Well you get a 10 slot backpack = ). Also 20 food/water/bandages. Not too bad,
  I'll cast a lot of it I assume.<br>
  <br>
  <i>Bristlebane's Bundle</i><br>
  Summons a Firecracer, a bunch of Beer, Some Cake, and umm.... err I forget the
  4th item *blush*<br>
  <br>
  <i>Quiver of Marr</i><br>
  I believe these arrows have a little higher damage than normal arrows, also
  have 75 range instead of 50. Summons 3 stacks of arrows and a quiver.<br>
  <br>
  <i>Bandoleer of Lucin</i><br>
  I'll have to look and see what this spell summons, I now forget *blush*<br>
  <br>
  <i>Pouch Of Quellios</i><br>
  Get ready to make lots of Monkish and Roguish friends. With this spell you get
  60 7/23 Shruriken with 100 range. They also have +3 to Agi and I think Dex.
  They are rogue and monk only however.<br>
  <br>
  <i>Muzzle of Mardu</i><br>
  Summons a haste mask. Gonna have to give it to brego or dravith to test = ).
  Pretty useless for an item summon at level 56 since every tank I know has a
  haste item. Last I checked there was no AC on the mask and no stat modifiers.
  So unless it's SLTW speed I doubt anyone but newbies will be asking for these.<br>
  <br>
  <b>OFFENSIVE AND DEFENSIVE SPELLS</b><br>
  Well here is everything else that doesn't fit into the above categories.<br>
  <br>
  <i>Scintilation</i><br>
  An AOE shock of swords. Kind of fun for clearing green trash. Good way to die
  still IMHO.<br>
  <br>
  <i>Malosi</i><br>
  We got a taste of it, now we ge it back. YAY!<br>
  <br>
  <i>Char</i><br>
  Its going to be everything I can do not to yel MANDER! every time I cast spell
  (pokemon joke, yes I'm ashamed of myself as well). Decent damage ratio,
  upgrade in our shock of flame line.<br>
  <br>
  <i>Phantom Armor</i><br>
  More AC, More Regen, More Cat's eye. Did you excpect something more?<br>
  <br>
  <i>Annul Magic</i><br>
  Dispell Magic upgrade.<br>
  <br>
  <i>Boon of Immolation</i><br>
  Dammit you mean I gotta wait until I'm 53 to get my first group damage shield?
  Well it costs as much as Lavashielding 3 tanks, I imagine I'll probably use it
  in groups with 2 or more tanks (because I'm lazy). Doesn't hit pets
  unfortunatly.<br>
  <br>
  <i>Shield of the Magi</i><br>
  More AC, More MR, More HP. Arch Sheilding upgrade.<br>
  <br>
  <i>Scars of Sigil</i><br>
  My favorite offensive spell. I've been training myself with bolt targeting
  just so this spell would be mine. At 150 mana, 450 damage and 4.0 casting time
  (2.0 recast), this spell is a machine gun. If you are outdoors you can try turning
  your back on your target, the bolt will take a longer path and you'll be able
  to get a few more into the air before the first hits.<br>
  <br>
  <i>Call of The Hero</i><br>
  YOU WILL NOT EVADE ME RILLO! Costs 1 pearl and 500 mana, is a slow cast and
  has a slow recycle time, but it will summon a group member to you from
  anywhere in the zone. I haven't tried it between zones yet, but I can't
  imagine it working as there is no good way to target it. I hope (although I
  doubt) this spell works in PoA, save us a fortune in coffin fees.<br>
  <br>
  <i>Sirocco</i><br>
  Huge damage rain spell, but rains are bugged and your pets are counted as
  targets hit. None the less a kind of fun spell outdoors vs tall targets
  (forest giants and such)<br>
  <br>
  <i>Eye Of Tallon</i><br>
  YES! Eye of Zomm Upgraded at last! It actually turns you invisible and makes
  and invisible eye, but I think this probably works to make mobs not see your
  eye for some odd reason. Also gives you see invis and some telescope effect.
  Interesting scouting spell, and good fun in Plane of Air. (A spiroc lord says,
  'TIRRANNA')<br>
  <br>
  <i>Cadeau of Flame</i><br>
  Bigger Flameshield...what did you expect?<br>
  <br>
  <i>Exile Summoned</i><br>
  More damage than banish summoned. Save this one for when hole opens.<br>
  <br>
  <i>Shock of Steel</i><br>
  Damage on this spell could be higher, but I love this line of spells and I
  imagine I'll be using this spell quite a bit. I think that at level 60 my
  offensive spell list will pretty much always be Shock of Steel and Scars of
  Sigil.<br>
  <br>
  <i>Malosini</i><br>
  Upgrade to Malosi. Faster cast time, lower mana, same debuff I believe.<br>
  <br>
  <i>Velocity</i><br>
  SoW for your pet...you just have to wait for level 58...Grr.<br>
  <br>
  <i>Manastorm</i><br>
  Interesting idea, it's aoe damage and mana tapping in a rain form. but still a
  rain spell so is subject to high resists and only a few waves. Quag is gonna
  see this spell, I owe him a few.<br>
  <br>
  <i>Seeking Flame of Seukor</i><br>
  Big Badda Boom! Make things blow up. Bolt upgrade, nice for a show I guess.<br>
  <br>
  <i>Aegis of Ro</i><br>
  Group Damage shield. Same damage as the last singe target damage shield for 3
  times the mana cost. but you can't shake a stick at 33 damage now can you?<br>
  <br>
  <i>Banishment</i><br>
  For the mere cost of a star ruby you can send one summoned creature back to
  where it came from...oh it takes it's corpse and exp with it...<br>
  <br>
  <i>Mala</i><br>
  Listed some places as Malo, actually read Mala in my spell book. The debuffs
  on this spell are pretty small, but it can't be saved against. Also last time
  I tried Malosini overrode Malo. So for 550 mana you can make your Malosini
  harder to resist. If you plan on doing this I recommend letting a friend cast
  one spell or the other to lower the mana costs.<br>
  <br>
  <br>
  Well that's it for magicians. Well all I know right now. Good luck exploring
  Kunark, hopefully my CD will be here soon and I'll be able to join you.<br>
  </font>
